Dual-listed Buffalo Coal recorded a profit from operations of R33.9-million for the year ended December 31, 2020, a 54% decrease year-on-year. Revenue from contracts with customers for the period was R321.3-million, a 19% decrease from the previous year. No dividend were declared or paid during the period. Buffalo owns 100% of Buffalo Coal Dundee, a South African company with an interest in two coal mines in South Africa.